msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> *It’s not enough to believe in something. You have to be ready to stand "
"for something, if you want change.* \n"
">\n"
"> *\\- Edward Snowden* \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:21
msgid ""
"The situation looks bleak and it feels like there is nothing you or I can "
"do."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:23
msgid ""
"This is not a predicament exclusive to our time. History can point us in the "
"direction of those who felt exactly the same. Ordinary people who, "
"constrained by injustice, took action to challenge those who held the power."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:25
msgid ""
"It is our right, and our moral obligation, to protest over unjust political, "
"economic or social conditions. Many of the rights we take for granted came "
"about as a result of protest—human rights, women’s rights, the rights of "
"workers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:27
msgid "It has always been a struggle to bring about change, but it can be achieved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is civil disobedience?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:31
msgid ""
"Civil disobedience is the active, non-violent refusal to accept the dictates "
"of governments. It informs them that unjust actions will be opposed and the "
"people will act illegally if pushed to do so."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:33
msgid ""
"Civil disobedience causes disruption and focuses attention, while forcing "
"debate with the aim of bringing about fundamental and progressive changes "
"within our societies and our world."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:35
msgid ""
"Acts of civil disobedience do not have to be extreme. We can all be "
"activists. Small actions can lead to larger ones, and can provide "
"inspiration to individuals who may be unsure where to funnel their "
"concerns. This in turn can help lay the pathway to further understanding and "
"global change."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:37
msgid ""
"These fifteen examples of civil disobedience span almost a century. From the "
"solitary action of a young Montgomery woman to the mass protests of "
"thousands in Scotland and Sudan, every one of these protestors remain united "
"in their demand for justice and call for a better world."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "1. Fight for Women's Suffrage: UK 1928"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:43
msgid ""
"Considered the inferior sex, women have no vote, no power and no say in how "
"their world is governed. In the face of injustice, women fight back."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deeds not Words."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:47
msgid ""
"The British fight for women’s suffrage (the legal right to vote) included "
"groups from the women’s labour movement and the moderate, "
"non-confrontational National Union of Women's Suffrage Societies "
"(NUWSS). Believing in civil disobedience, the NUWSS disrupted Parliament, "
"chained themselves to railings, distributed pamphlets and organised "
"demonstrations and lectures."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:49
msgid ""
"The more militant Women’s Social and Political Union (WSPU) were prepared to "
"use any tactic necessary. This included often violent, direct action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:51
msgid ""
"When arrested, Suffragettes offered further resistance by going on [hunger "
"strike](https://www.historyextra.com/period/edwardian/cat-mouse-force-feeding-suffragettes-hunger-strike/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:53
msgid ""
"Although Suffragettes are often portrayed as originating from the ruling "
"classes, thousands of [brave working class "
"women](https://www.bl.uk/votes-for-women/articles/women-quite-unknown-working-class-women-in-the-suffrage-movement) "
"made huge personal sacrifices for the movement, their punishments often more "
"barbaric than those of higher societal standing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:55
msgid ""
"Not all women could afford the sacrifice. Many were breadwinners, or worked "
"long shifts as servants or in factories, returning home to care for children "
"and keep the house."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:57
msgid ""
"The 1918 Representation of the People Act granted women over the age of 30 "
"the right to vote in Britain. Full suffrage, that is the right to vote over "
"the age of 21, in accordance with male voting, was passed in 1928."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:59
msgid ""
"The Suffragette victory in Britain followed years of protest, struggle and "
"inconceivable hardship. Each woman chose her role and every role was "
"important."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:61
msgid ""
"Thirty five years previously, in 1893, the women of New Zealand were first "
"to win the vote. Saudi Arabia granted women suffrage [in "
"2015](https://www.verdict.co.uk/womens-suffrage-across-world/). Revolution "
"may take decades, but when it eventually comes, it can have an everlasting "
"impact on the course of history."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:63
msgid ""
"![Painting of "
"sufragette](/assets/uploads/d428b3e1-71f9-4fe1-bbfc-ff96e869a681.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-11-03-civil-disobedience-examples.md:65
#, no-wrap
